      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAFFETTIERA (5) resumes and was last seen in the Group 3 Blue Sapphire Stakes. Went close in a Cranbourne Open 3 prior and placed at Geelong at her only fresh start. Has two jumpouts under the saddle and will get every chance from the inside barrier. SHE'S MY EX (4) is an improving galloper and she has jumped out well since her solid effort at Flemington is stronger. Craig Williams sticks from that and has won twice on the filly. Led last time and is a big chance. INNOCENT ENUFF (2) comfortably won a 66 at Crambourne off a near miss at Moe. The claim helps offset some of the weight rise and the speedy galloper will probably look the winner at some point. PARADISE ISLAND (9) shouldn't trouble these.",
